{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_019yue2m9vuHvyXZMEfGNsCb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01VwkfKZtobtCqns9aiMV7US","name":"StructuredOutput","input":{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Request sent to external API includes complete list of valid taxonomy labels","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This tests request construction. A real failure is that taxonomy labels are omitted from the request payload. A mock of the external API can inspect the call arguments to verify the labels are present. No integration with actual API infrastructure is needed to catch this logic error.","test_description":"Mock the external API, call the module with a test document, capture and inspect the request arguments passed to the mocked call, and assert that all taxonomy labels (legal, technical, financial, other) are present in the request payload.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.75,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When API returns label outside taxonomy, module returns \"unknown\" instead of forwarding it","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This tests output validation and error handling. A real failure is that unexpected API responses bypass the validation check and propagate invalid labels to callers. A mock API configured to return an invalid label can verify the module sanitizes it without needing a real API.","test_description":"Configure the mocked external API to return a classification label that is not in the fixed taxonomy, call the module with a test document, and assert that the module returns exactly \"unknown\" rather than forwarding the invalid label.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.8,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Classification result for same document is identical across repeated calls","minim