behavior_id":5,"description":"When API signals rate limit, module waits and retries instead of returning error","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior involves coordinating multiple components: detecting a rate-limit error, executing a wait, and retrying the request. The real failure is not just missing retry logic but also broken timing or coordination between steps. A pure in-process mock of the API response alone would miss the failure where the module retries immediately without waiting. Testing the wait-and-retry coordination requires either Integration-level testing with a stateful mock that tracks call sequencing and enforces timing, or Unit-level testing with time mocking infrastructure. Integration testing with a mock API that fails on first call(s) and succeeds on retry is the most straightforward approach.","test_description":"Create a mock of the external API that returns a rate-limit error on the first call and a successful classification on the second call. Set a configured wait duration. Call the module with a test document and verify that it catches the rate-limit error, waits for the configured duration, retries the request, and returns the eventual successful classification result rather than immediately failing to the caller.","plan_consistent":true,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.6,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13606,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13606},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ad870a26-11a7-4877-a153-1106a07b4949","uuid":"297c9d37-e693-4d7f-9455-f69260874198"}
